node.text: They may not be everyone's favorite vegetable, but beets are more complex than you think. Give these controversial roots a try in desserts, salads, and even cocktails.

node.title: The Science Behind Beets | What's Eating Dan

node.text: Inspired by @icecreamgracies in Somerville, MA we steep whole coffee beans so that they contribute great coffee flavor without adding the coffee color. Tap the link in our bio to get the recipe for White Coffee Chip Ice Cream.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 31, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: For the best crispy seared salmon, start it skin side down in a cold skillet. The skin protects the fish from drying out, and it releases fat into the pan, which is then used to sear the second side until it is golden brown. Tap the link in our bio to get the recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 31, 2021.

node.text: Roasting whole beets can take up to 2 hours, and who wants to do that during the summertime? This recipe takes a fraction of the time. Tap the link in our bio to sign up for a free trial and get the recipe for Beet Salad with Spiced Yogurt and Watercress.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 31, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: “This is, hands down, the best key lime pie I have ever tasted,” -Sophie M. Tap the link in our bio to sign up for a free trial and get the recipe for Key Lime Pie.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Tomato season is upon us. Showcase their vibrant color and sweet flavor in a simple tomato and cheese tart. Tap the link in our bio to sign up for a free trial and get the recipe for Torta di Pomodoro.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Staggering the cooking of the dark and white meat ensures that the collagen in the dark meat breaks down before the white meat dries out. Tap the link in our bio to sign up for a free trial and get the recipe for Braised Chicken with Basil and Tomato by @lan_cooks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: To create garlic bread with garlic flavor that’s prominent but not harsh, we use both fresh garlic and garlic powder (and plenty of butter). Tap the link in our bio to get the recipe for Really Good Garlic Bread.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 30, 2021. May be an image of french fries.

node.text: The best air fryer is easy to use, can fit enough food for four people, and can be used in place of  a traditional oven or toaster oven. Which model is our top pick? Tap the link in our bio to read our review.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: When it’s hot and humid, it doesn’t get much more refreshing than sweet, juicy melon. With additions like cheese, olives, fresh herbs, and more, we put a savory twist on these summer fruits. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about our melon salad recipes by @algcooks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 29, 2021.

node.text: To achieve juicy pork patties for our bún chả , we mix baking soda into the meat which raises the pH, helping it to retain moisture and brown during the longer grilling time. Tap the link in our bio to get the recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 29, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: If you’re looking for a cold summer dessert that isn’t ice cream, our chocolate semifreddo is a unique alternative. Tap the link in our bio to sign up for a free trial and get the recipe by @appetito611.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cook's Illustrated on July 29, 2021. May be an image of dessert and text that says 'ASK PAUL What's the Difference? Bread and Ice Cream'.

node.text: Before you laugh, the structures of these two foods may have more in common than you think. Tap the link in our bio to learn more from our science editor.
